snippet.textDisplay:
NONONONONO! Not "every single person" can get on the internet Timothy. The internet is a privilege & not available to "every single person". Your white privilege is showing buddy. Go spend some more time in third world countries & perhaps expose your self to more than a beach vacation in these third world countries you wist. Make an effort to educate yourself.
Cuba doesn't have internet as readily available as the US, it is not possible to use mobile internet in that country. 
In Uzbekistan a country with a total population of 32 million, approximately 9 million people can connect to the internet. 
As I understand it the general population of Eritrea has no internet access. 
& JIC you're one of those people who disregard that bc "we're talking about the US" please allow me to educate you on the "digital divide". I'll use the "educational gap" between students in urban & suburban areas vs rural students in the US as an example. It’s estimated that 6.5 million students nationwide don’t have the broadband Internet access. Let's use Montana as an example. More than 720,000 Montanans do not have access the internet at broadband speeds. I'll not single out any add't states just look up the FCC's "The Connect America Fund" & check out the map if visuals help. They've made some progress but many public schools in rural America still don't have internet let alone broadband.
